name: Charles X and Gustaf V of Sweden
obverse: Bust of Charles X facing right and bust of Gustaf V facing left. Each bust is in a circle. Behind the circles are two crossed branches.
reverse: A maiden wearing a crown holds a shield with the coat of arms of Sweden and holds a branch up. Four other women present garlands to the maiden. A lion lies next to the maiden. In the background is a coastline with the sun rising.
description: Charles X Gustav of Sweden was King of Sweden from 1654 - 1660.
Gustaf V of Sweden was King of Sweden from 1907 - 1950.
